comments: Allen (CLE) establishes himself in Anunoby?s (TOR) path and does not deliver contact.
Siakam (TOR) is moving alongside Mobley?s (CLE) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.

Mobley (CLE) gathers the ball in the air as he comes to a jump stop and establishes his left foot as his pivot. Mobley then lifts and replants his pivot foot before he begins his upward shooting motion.
Anunoby (TOR) slides his hand across and off Allen's (CLE) upper body as they engage during the rebound.
Allen (CLE) deflects the ball out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to TOR.
As Siakam (TOR) and LeVert (CLE) come together during the drive, Siakam releases from the marginal contact.
After the ball becomes loose, Mitchell (CLE) and Anunoby (TOR) come together in pursuit of the loose ball, and incidental contact occurs.
Anunoby (TOR) deflects the ball out of bounds.
Osman (CLE) splits his feet at the start of his dribble.
VanVleet (TOR) swipes down and across Osman?s (CLE) front, which affects his driving shot attempt.
VanVleet (TOR) brings his hands toward LeVert (CLE) and marginal contact occurs as VanVleet releases away to roll.
Siakam (TOR) releases from the contact with LeVert (CLE) during the pick, and the contact is marginal.
Mitchell (CLE) moves alongside Siakam?s (TOR) path and maintains a legal guarding position as incidental contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Osman (CLE) does not establish himself in VanVleet's (TOR) path when he delivers contact during the dribble hand-off.
Barnes (TOR) gathers the ball and establishes his left foot as his pivot, which he maintains as he legally pivots during his shot attempt.
Siakam (TOR) delivers body contact to Mitchell (CLE) and affects Mitchell?s SQBR during the drive.
LeVert (CLE) makes marginal lower body contact with Trent Jr. (TOR) as he splits the double team.
LeVert (CLE) makes marginal contact with Trent Jr. (TOR) as he completes his intended pass.
Mitchell (CLE) commits a take foul on Banton (TOR) as he passes.
VanVleet (TOR) is awarded the timeout prior to a 5-second violation occurring.
LeVert (CLE) commits a take foul on Trent Jr. (TOR).
Anunoby (TOR) commits a take foul on LeVert (CLE). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
LeVert (CLE) deflects the pass out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to TOR.
Barnes (TOR) releases the pass prior to marginal contact occurring from LeVert (CLE).
After the made basket, Achiuwa (TOR) interferes with the ball and prevents it from promptly being put back into play.
VanVleet (TOR) legally contests Mitchell?s (CLE) jump shot attempt.
